  villagerComplaint:
  - Theres not enough water to water the crops!
  actualRootCause: The central well is structurally compromised, leaking water into
    the soil
  who: The village's crop farmers
  what: The well is leaking into the soil
  where: At the village's central well
  when: Every time water is drawn
  why: The well's structure is cracked
  whoDistractors:
  - The village blacksmith
  - The traveling merchants
  - The town guards
  whatDistractors:
  - Pests are eating the crops
  - The crops were planted too late
  - There's been no rain for weeks
  whereDistractors:
  - In the crop fields themselves
  - Downstream at the river
  - In the village grain storehouse
  whenDistractors:
  - Only during the winter months
  - Once a year at harvest
  - After last week's storm
  whyDistractors:
  - Farmers are overusing water
  - The irrigation channels are blocked
  - The crops need more sunlight
  trivialSolutionName: Patch the bucket and rope
  optimalSolutionName: Rebuild the pulley and pipe filter system
  trivialReflectionText: The patch worked for now, but the root cause remains. The
    well will fail again soon...
  optimalReflectionText: Great work! Rebuilding the pulley system fixed the root
    cause. Water flows properly now.
